e%20got%20divorced%20one%20month%20later%2C%20although%20they%20remained%20in%20close%20contact%20for%20Basterra%20Porto's%20sake%2C%20The%20Guardian%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20divorce%2C%20the%20girl%20told%20her%20school%20headmistress%20that%20her%20mother%20had%20been%20giving%20her%20a%20%26quot%3Bwhite%20powder%26quot%3B%20for%20her%20allergies%2C%20which%20was%20making%20her%20extremely%20tired%2C%20the%20Spanish%20newspaper%20La%20Voz%20de%20Galicia%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20reported%20Asunta%20missing%20on%20September%2021%2C%202013%2C%20and%20her%20body%20was%20found%20a%20day%20later.%20Police%20arrested%20Porto%20and%20Basterra%20when%20the%20same%20type%20of%20orange%20rope%20that%20was%20used%20to%20tie%20up%20Asunta's%20limbs%20was%20found%20in%20the%20trash%20at%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etheir%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20where%20Porto%20and%20Basterra%20are%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlfonso%20Basterra%20was%20given%20an%2018-year%20prison%20sentence%20for%20murder%2C%20which%20he's%20still%20serving%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221874%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Alfonso%20Basterra%20was%20arrested%20on%20suspicion%20of%20murdering%20his%20daughter%2C%20Asunta%20Basterra%2C%20in%20September%202013.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66250cfd83c8ec6e153064e8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221406%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAlfonso%20Basterra%20was%20arrested%20on%20suspicion%20of%20murdering%20his%20daughter%2C%20Asunta%20Basterra%2C%20in%20September%202013.%20%3Cp%3EEuropa%20Press%20Entertainment%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20trial%20in%202015%2C%20the%20jury%20established%20that%20the%20parents%20repeatedly%20drugged%20Asunta%20over%20the%20summer%20of%202013%20and%20then%20strangled%20her%20to%20death%2C%20Spanish%20outlet%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.elmundo.es%2Fsociedad%2F2015%2F10%2F30%2F5