li%3EThe%20incident%20exposes%20a%20loophole%20in%20the%20safety%20of%20delivery%20app%20services.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20food%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgolden-age-gig-work-instacart-doordash-delivery-jobs-over-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edelivery%20driver%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20grievous%20bodily%20harm%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeliveroo-driver-bit-off-customer-thumb-company-not-liable-app-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebiting%20off%20a%20customer's%20thumb%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20been%20spotted%20delivering%20food%20again%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fuk-england-hampshire-68928464%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20BBC%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20woman%2C%20who%2C%20according%20to%20a%20court%20document%2C%20is%20named%20Jeniffer%20Rocha%2C%20was%20delivering%20food%20for%20the%20UK%20delivery%20app%20Deliveroo%20in%20December%202022%20when%20she%20got%20into%20an%20argument%20with%20Stephen%20Jenkinson%2C%20the%20customer%20she%20was%20delivering%20pizza%20to%2C%20per%20the%20BBC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJenkinson%20told%20the%20BBC%20that%20Rocha%20had%20arrived%20at%20the%20wrong%20location%20and%20that%20when%20he%20went%20to%20collect%20his%20order%2C%20he%20didn't%20bring%20his%20phone%2C%20leading%20to%20an%20argument%20about%20his%20delivery%20code%20number.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJenkinson%20told%20the%20outlet%20that%20he%20raised%20his%20hand%20to%20Rocha's%20motorcycle%20helmet%2C%20and%20she%20then%20bit%20his%20thumb.%20%26quot%3BShe'd%20taken%20it%20clean%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20the%20BBC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJenkinson%2C%20a%20plumber%2C%20previously%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fuk-68558464%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20had%20been%20unable%20to%20work%20since%20then%20and%20was%20financially%20%26quot%3Bruined.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20that%20he'd%20had%20months%20of%20surgery%20to%20reconstruct%20his%20thumb%20using%20part%20of%20his%20big%20toe%20and%20that%20he%20had%20no%20sensation%20in%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20Rocha%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20one%20count%20of%20grievous%20bodily%20harm%20without%20intent.%20She's%20set%20to%20be%20sentenced%20on%20Friday%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Winchester%20Crown%20Court%20confirmed%20to%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20concerning%20loophole%20in%20app%20safety%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Rocha%20delivered%20to%20Jenkinson%2C%20she%20was%20working%20as%20a%20substitute%20for%20another%20rider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDeliveroo%20classes%20its%20riders%20as%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeliveroo-self-employed-workers-rights-tribunal%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindependent%20contractors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%20they're%20self-employed%2C%20and%20because%20of%20this%2C%20they're%20able%20to%20appoint%20other%20people%20as%20substitutes.%20The%20substitutes%20can%20complete%20deliveries%20using%20a%20rider's%20account%20without%20registering.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20incident%20highlights%20the%20concerns%20around%20the%20potential%20dangers%20of%20substitute%20drivers%2C%20given%20that%20it%20can%20be%20hard%20for%20delivery%20companies%20to%20verify%20the%20identities%20of%20these%20substitutes.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Deliveroo%20riders%20have%20to%20be%20over%2018%20with%20no%20unspent%20criminal%20convictions%2C%20it's%20historically%20been%20up%20to%20individual%20riders%2C%20not%20Deliveroo%20itself%2C%20to%20check%20that%20their%20substitutes%20meet%20this%20criteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Deliveroo%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20company%20had%20%26quot%3Bimmediately%26quot%3B%20canceled%20the%20account%20Rocha%20was%20using%20when%20the%20%26quot%3Bterrible%20incident%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20the%20attack%20on%20Jenkinson%20%E2%80%94%20occurred.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20after%20Rocha%20appeared%20in%20court%2C%20the%20BBC%20spotted%20her%20twice%20collecting%20food%20for%20delivery%20on%20her%20moped%2C%20it%20reported.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20second%20occasion%2C%20on%20April%2018%2C%20it%20said%20that%20the%20manager%20of%20the%20takeaway%20she%20collected%20an%20order%20from%20said%20that%20she%20was%20delivering%20it%20for%20Deliveroo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Deliveroo%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20it%20had%20also%20canceled%20an%20alternative%20account%20that%20Rocha%20was%20using.%20It's%20unclear%20whether%20this%20was%20her%20own%20account%20or%20whether%20she%20was%20delivering%20as%20a%20substitute%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20take%20our%20responsibilities%20extremely%20seriously%20and%20are%20committed%20to%20preventing%20misuse%20of%20our%20platform%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20strengthened%20our%20processes%20and%20recently%20introduced%20a%20new%20registration%20process%20and%20identity%20verification%20technology%20for%20substitute%20riders.%26quot%3B%20This%20includes%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Fgovernment%2Fnews%2Fdeliveroo-just-eat-and-uber-eats-to-enhance-security-checks-to-prevent-illegal-working%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eright-to-work%20checks%3C%2Fa%3E%20rolled%20out%20by%20Deliveroo%20in%20April.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdelivery-driver-bit-off-customers-thumb-seen-delivering-food-again-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714654778000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66336abbec0c6965690009a7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdelivery-driver-bit-off-customers-thumb-seen-delivering-food-again-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20the%20time%20of%20the%20attack%2C%2