-against-ukrianian-troops-us-claims-13127381%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sun%20Unleashes%20Extremely%20Powerful%20Solar%20Flare%2C%20Pacific%20Region%20Hit%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAn%20extremely%20powerful%20solar%20flare%20triggered%20widespread%20radio%20blackouts%20across%20the%20Pacific%20region%20this%20week%2C%20according%20to%20a%20report%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.space.com%2Fnear-x-class-solar-flare-april-30-2024-video%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Espace.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20eruption%20lasted%2012%20minutes%20on%20April%2030%20and%20released%20near%20X-class%20solar%20flares%2C%20the%20most%20powerful.%20As%20per%20NASA%2C%20solar%20flares%20happen%20when%20powerful%20magnetic%20fields%20in%20and%20around%20the%20Sun%20reconnect.%20They%20are%20created%20when%20magnetic%20energy%20builds%20up%20in%20the%20solar%20atmosphere%20and%20is%20released.%20Flares%20are%20classified%20according%20to%20their%20strength.%20After%20the%20most%20powerful%20X-class%2C%20there%20are%20M-class%20flares%20that%20are%2010%20times%20less%20powerful%2C%20followed%20by%20C-class%20and%20finally%2C%20B-class%20flares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20April%2030%20flare%20clocked%20in%20at%20M9.53%2C%20according%20to%20spaceweatherlive.com%2C%20measured%20by%20NASA's%20GOES-16%20satellite%2C%20which%20puts%20it%20just%20a%20fraction%20below%20an%20X-class%20solar%20flare.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20ionized%20the%20upper%20atmosphere%20while%20hitting%20the%20Earth%20on%20April%2030.%20%26quot%3BMariners%20and%20ham%20radio%20operators%20may%20have%20noticed%20loss%20of%20signal%20below%2020%20MHz%20for%20as%20much%20as%2030%20minutes%20after%20the%20flare's%20peak%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3Espaceweather.com%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20powerful%20solar%20flare%20erupted%20from%20sunspot%20region%20AR3654%2C%20the%20most%20powerful%20eruption%20from%20this%20region%20yet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20always%20exciting%20when%20a%20sunspot%20region%20lives%20up%20to%20its%20potential.%20AR3654%20has%20just%20done%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20solar%20scientist%20Alex%20Young%20posted%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rate%20of%20eruption%20of%20flares%20has%20increased%20in%20the%20past%20few%20years%20since%20the%20Sun%20approaches%20solar%20maximum%2C%20the%20peak%20of%20solar%20activity%20during%20its%20approximately%2011-year%20solar%20cycle.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESolar%20flares%20travel%20at%20the%20speed%20of%20light%20and%20can%20impact%20spacecraft%2C%20satellites%20and%20some%20ground-based%20stations.%20We%20come%20to%20know%20about%20a%20solar%20flare%20because%20agencies%20like%20NASA%2C%20NOAA%20and%20the%20US%20Air%20Force%20Weather%20Agency%20(AFWA)%20are%20monitoring%20the%20Sun%20closely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20NASA%20experts%20have%20clarified%20that%20so-called%20%26quot%3Bkiller%20flares%26quot%3B%20do%20not%20exist.%20The%20flares%20can%20cause%20significant%20damage%20on%20Earth%20and%20disrupt%20the%20technological%20world%2C%20they%20don't%20contain%20enough%20energy%20to%20do%20any%20lasting%20damage%20to%20Earth%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1714641000000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2F1o7v2jf8_solar-flare-_625x300_20_December_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fsun-unleashes-extremely-powerful-solar-flare-pacific-region-hit-5571435%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20April%2030%20flare%20clocked%20in%20at%20M9.53%2C%20according%20to%20spaceweatherlive.com%2C%20measured%20by%20NASA's%20GOES-16%20satellite%2C%20which%20puts%20it%20just%20a%20fraction%20below%20the%20most%20powerful%20X-class%20solar%20flare.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fsun-unleashes-extremely-powerful-solar-flare-pacific-region-hit-5571435%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscien